properties.areaDesc: Utah's Dixie and Zion National Park
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 2 at 2:32PM MST until February 5 at 4:00AM MST by NWS Salt Lake City UT
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest gusts up to 55 mph this evening, shifting to
the northwest late tonight and Monday morning. Winds will
diminish for a time Monday afternoon and evening, before gusting
out of the north up to 55 mph across outlying Dixie Monday night
through Tuesday night.

* WHERE...Utahs Dixie and Zion National Park.

* WHEN...From 7 PM this evening to 4 AM MST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Strong crosswinds will create hazardous driving conditions for
high profile vehicles and those towing trailers. Wind sensitive
operations will be impacted.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

The strong winds will create dangerous boating conditions on area
lakes. These winds will create very choppy water and generate
large waves which could capsize or swamp small craft. For your
personal safety, operators of small craft are urged to postpone
their outings until the winds subside.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT FROM 7 PM THIS EVENING TO 4 AM MST WEDNESDAY
